<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gruffydd</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am a level 26 Shaman looking for a place to hunt with good loot so I can buy dufrenite for my Totemic Armour Quest. Any suggestions?.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Methis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">well it was sorta slow, but from 19-22 I camped the guard at the lavastorm/forest zone.  got really good exp kiting him, and he drops a bronze longsword that you can sell for 3pp if your char is decent.  I got over 500pp doing this for 3 levels.  Don't know if he'll still give exp for you at your level however</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Papillion</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hunting Hill Giants in Rathe Mtns is fairly lucrative - they can drop up to 28 pp total, so with a small, good group you can do ok.  Plus HG toes are used for mages' focus items - frost giant toes net 7pp from vendor - don't know about HG toes.  Heard someone auctioning 70pp for Frost Giant toes...  Save a few HG toes and sell.  Also Sarnaks in Kunark - GREAT xp and ok loot.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jarren</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">At Lev 26 the Hill Giants in the Rathe Mountains might be a tad harsh unless you're in a VERY GOOD group.  However, the Mountain Giants in Warsliks Woods (Kunark) will be very doable to someone at your level.<P>They do not drop coin.  However, they have various items that can be sold to merchants for about 10pp.  Sometimes, you can even get these cool earrings that sell for almost 1kpp.<P><BR>Jarren</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">herbie34</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sorry, HG's aren't do-able at 26..spells stop being entirely resisted at 28. They do drop up to 48pp as well, not including gold/silver/copper. At 26 your best bet for loot would be to forget loot till around 30 and sit on Icy Orcs in Everfrost for a couple of days and lvl quickly to 30. Then go get into a HG group. You can make over 100pp in an hour with a decent group there. Also, if you really need loot and don't want to take the time to lvl there's always the bandits in WK, turn in the sashes to Cheesgard in S.Qeynos..U can net 100pp in a couple of hours...or if you don't mind being KOS to druids, kill treants. Great loot there also.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lysensia Mystica</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mammoths in Everfrost. The tusks were worth 10pp each at my shaman guild in Halas.<P>Advice - bind just outside the shaman guild, then collect as many tusks as possible and gate back to sell. They are heavy and at one point I was so encumbered my agi was 1 !! Lucky for gate that I didn't actually have to run any where in a hurry  <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif"> Then as you run back you can bank all your cash before collecting more tusks  <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Eavis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">the giant fort in Frontier Mts. is very good also excellent XP and good loot with the weapons they drop most sell to vendor for 10pp some for up to 70pp<P>Eavis</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vranje</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"><BR> Why not get a group and go to SolA. Not only do you get good loot but that is where your durefrite stuff drops. Excellent exp. to be had in there also.<P> Vranje<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">milidar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ok you will be so amazed if you go to high keep and hunt gobbies down there....a bit tuff to get into a group but if you do youll make about 200pp a night from selling the loot they drop.  They drop all different types of ore, bronze (as in armor) also drops down there, another thing they drop is amazingly fine steel goes for up to 5pp to vendors and also drop about 3pp every 2-3 pops.  Since the banker is about 20 feet away and you dont have to zone you can save every copper and dont worry about becomming encombered </FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
